<doc id="319698" wikidata="Q209270" url="?curid=319698" title="Appenzell (village)">
<text>Appenzell () is a municipality and village, though considered as a town by the FSO, and the capital of the canton of Appenzell Innerrhoden in Switzerland. Appenzell has no municipal government of its own; rather, the different parts of Appenzell belong to and are governed by the districts Appenzell and Schwende-Rüte. Because of that, for firefighting, energy and water, the village Appenzell has a special-purpose municipality, the Feuerschaugemeinde.

== History ==
In 1071 the village was referred to as &quot;Abbacella&quot;. By 1223 this changed to &quot;Abbatiscella&quot;, meaning the Abbot&#x27;s cell. This refers to the abbot of the Abbey of Saint Gall.

The buildings in the village core, the parish church, the 1563 town hall, the &quot;Salesis&quot; house, the ruins of Castle Clanx and the state archives with the administration building are listed as heritage sites of national significance.

== Notable people ==
* Roman Signer (born 1938 in Appenzell) a visual artist who works in sculpture, art installations photography, and video.

== Gallery ==

